  <div class="project-body">
    <p class="section-title">What students learn</p>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;margin-bottom:1rem;">Multiple GPIO outputs, sequential state logic, thinking in "states" — foundation of state machines.</p>

    <p class="section-title">Wiring connections</p>
    <table class="wiring-table">
      <tr><th>Component Pin</th><th>ESP32 Pin</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="pin-comp">Red LED Anode</td><td class="pin-esp">GPIO 2</td><td>Through 220Ω resistor</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="pin-comp">Yellow LED Anode</td><td class="pin-esp">GPIO 4</td><td>Through 220Ω resistor</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="pin-comp">Green LED Anode</td><td class="pin-esp">GPIO 5</td><td>Through 220Ω resistor</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="pin-comp">All LED Cathodes</td><td class="pin-esp">GND</td><td>Share a common GND</td></tr>
